  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I connect my PC's internet to my Windows Phone via USB or via Bluetooth?",
  "response": "Connecting your Windows Phone to your PC's internet via USB or Bluetooth involves a few steps. Below, I\u2019ll outline how to do this using both methods.\n\n### Using USB Tethering\n\n1. **Connect the Phone to PC**:\n   - Use a USB cable to connect your Windows Phone to your PC.\n\n2. **Enable USB Tethering on Windows Phone**:\n   - Go to **Settings** on your Windows Phone.\n   - Tap on **Network & Wireless**.\n   - Select **Mobile hotspot** or similar options (the exact wording might vary based on your Windows Phone version).\n   - Enable the mobile hotspot or USB tethering.\n\n3. **Set Up the Connection on Your PC**:\n   - On your PC, go to **Settings**.\n   - Navigate to **Network & Internet**.\n   - Look for **Ethernet** or **Network Connections**.\n   - You should see the phone as a network connection. Select this connection to use the internet.\n\n4. **Test the Internet**:\n   - Open a web browser on your PC and check if you can access the internet.\n\n### Using Bluetooth Tethering\n\n1. **Pair Your Devices**:\n   - On your Windows Phone, go to **Settings** > **Devices** > **Bluetooth** and make sure Bluetooth is turned on.\n   - On your PC, go to **Settings** > **Devices** > **Bluetooth & other devices** and turn on Bluetooth. Click on **Add Bluetooth or other device** to start pairing.\n   - Select your Windows Phone from the list and follow any on-screen prompts to complete the pairing.\n\n2. **Enable Bluetooth Tethering on Windows Phone**:\n   - On your Windows Phone, go to **Settings** > **Network & Wireless** > **Mobile hotspot**.\n   - Enable the Bluetooth tethering option (if available).\n\n3. **Connect to the Internet via Bluetooth on your PC**:\n   - On your PC, go to **Settings** > **Network & Internet** > **Bluetooth** settings.\n   - Find your paired Windows Phone, right-click on it, and choose the option to connect using the internet (this can also be labeled as \"Connect using Internet\").\n\n4. **Test the Internet**:\n   - Open a web browser on your PC to see if the internet is accessible.\n\n### Troubleshooting\n- If you encounter issues, make sure both devices are updated, and check your PC\u2019s network settings.\n- Be aware that using USB or Bluetooth tethering can incur data charges on your mobile plan if you are not connected to Wi-Fi.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to share your PC\u2019s internet connection with your Windows Phone via USB or Bluetooth.",
